<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   MiG-29 Purchase Unaffected by Russian Stand on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MiG-29 Purchase Unaffected by Russian Stand on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805135394 Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network in Malay 
1300 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Radio Malaysia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Malay </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has no intention of canceling its 
purchase of Russian-made MiG-29 fighters even though Russia has 
yet to adopt a clear stand on the Bosnia-Herzegovina issue. 
Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said this to 
reporters after the inauguration of the building housing UMNO's 
[United Malays National Organization] Pramu Branch in Pekan, 
Pahang. He said Malaysia should maintain its credibility, or 
else other countries will certainly wonder whether future 
decisions will be based on good practices or on some political 
stand. He added that the decision to buy the aircraft stands 
even though Malaysia is not pleased with Russia's position on 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina issue. This is because Malaysia needs to 
modernize its air force and strengthen its ability to defend the 
nation's airspace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

