<H3> <TI>   Central Bank's Gold, Foreign Exchange Reserves Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank's Gold, Foreign Exchange Reserves Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805070794 Kuala Lumpur NEW STRAITS TIMES in English 6 May 
94 p 16 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805070794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur NEW STRAITS TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bank Negara's [Central Bank's] gold and foreign 
exchange and other reserves including SDI (special drawing 
rights) amounted to RM89,986.72 million as at Jan. 31, 1994. It 
was RM89,875.43 million a fortnight earlier and RM76,474.43 
million at end December 1993 
  A Bank Negara statement said total assets and liabilities 
eased slightly to RM116,215.81 million from RM116,331.73 million 
a fortnight earlier but higher than the RM100,299.47 million as 
at Dec. 31,1993. 
  Loans and advances were higher at RM2,552.34 million from 
RM2,479.17 million two weeks ago and RM2,637.07 million a month 
earlier. 
  The bank's holdings of bills dlscounted amounted to 
RM3,391.97 million. It was RM3,450.35 million two weeks earlier 
and RM3,523.94 million a month ago. 
  Currency in circulation amounted to RM16,626.48 million 
against RM14,835.48 million two weeks ago and RM14,649.04 
million a month earlier. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

