<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Draft Accords With Other Nations Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Draft Accords With Other Nations Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905130394 Seoul YONHAP in English 1142 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 9 (YONHAP) -- The cabinet on Monday 
approved a number of draft agreements to be signed with foreign 
countries. 
  They included a draft double taxation prevention agreement 
set to be concluded with Vietnam within the month at the 
earliest. 
  Others were a draft agreement on the establishment of a 
Korea-China Industrial Cooperation Council: a draft memorandum 
on Korea-China Civil Aeronautical Cooperation and Development: 
a draft Korea-Argentina investment guarantee agreement: and a 
draft memorandum on Korea-Philippine Defense Industry 
Cooperation. 
  Meanwhile, South Korea and the Uzbekistan Republic initialed 
a bilateral aviation agreement in Seoul Monday. The agreement 
is expected to be signed during President Kim Yong-sam's visit 
to the Republic early next month. 

</TEXT>

