<DOCNO> FBIS4-52399 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas090_q_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-090 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vo Van Kiet on Diplomatic Ties With U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vo Van Kiet on Diplomatic Ties With U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0205043194 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0100 GMT 2 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0205043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vietnam's prime minister, Vo Van Kiet, said his 
country is ready for the restoration of full diplomatic 
relations with the United States at any time. Speaking to Radio 
Australia's Hanoi correspondent, Christopher Kramer, Mr. Kiet 
said normalized relations would be in the interests of not only 
the two countries, but the entire region. He said full 
diplomatic ties were inevitable. 
  Mr. Kiet committed his government to continuing political 
reforms, which, he said, paved the way for economic reforms. 
But asked if Vietnam was moving toward a multiparty democracy, 
Mr. Kiet said the question was never raised because the priority 
was to make the country rich and build a civilized society. 

</TEXT>

