<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Committee Denounces South Nuclear Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Denounces South Nuclear Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0513 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Nuclear Development in S. Korea Denounced" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Chong Sin-hyok, 
vice-chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of 
the Fatherland, issued a statement to the press Saturday, in 
which he scathingly denounced the South Korean puppet clique's 
moves to develop nuclear arms as a heinous, anti-national crime 
intended to inflict a nuclear holocaust upon the entire fellow 
countrymen and turn the 3,000-ri national territory into a 
barren land. 
  He charged that the South Korean puppet clique have 
already acquired the capability to make nuclear weapons and 
produced and concealed several nukes in secret. 
  The statement said: 
  The International Atomic Energy Agency, reduced to a maid of 
the United States, has connived at the military nuclear 
facilities in South Korea, not announcing the result of 
investigation of them, while openly taking issue with the DPRK's 
experimental reactor for a peaceful use. This clearly shows 
that the agency is devoid of impartiality. 
  If the United States and the IAEA Secretariat have 
willingness to prevent proliferation of nuclear weapons and keep 
peace on the globe, they should, first of all, pay due attention 
to the South Korean puppets' nuclear development on an extremely 
dangerous stage and urgently take an appropriate step against it. 
  The statement earnestly called upon the entire fellow 
countrymen in the North and the South of Korea and overseas to 
actively turn out in the just struggle to check and frustrate 
the South Korean puppet clique's dangerous development of 
nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

