<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-sam Remarks on Peace Proposal Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Yong-sam Remarks on Peace Proposal Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0705052094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0506 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705052094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Shameless Utterances Reversing Black and White" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 7 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim Yong-sam 
at "Chongwadae" [presidential offices] on May 4 blared that the 
North was "engaged in nuclear development" targeted against 
South Korea and that the North was "violating the truce 
agreement, not abandoning its ambition for communization of the 
South". He also slandered the North's recent negotiation 
proposal vis-a-vis the United States to replace the Korean 
Armistice Agreement with a peace agreement and establish a new 
peace arrangement. 
  Branding them as shameless remarks reversing black and 
white, 
motivated by an intention to slander and harm the North, a news 
analyst of NODONG SINMUN today says: 
  They who are hell bent on moves to plunge the nation into a 
holocaust of nuclear war, acting as a shock brigade of outside 
forces in their "nuclear racket" to isolate and stifle the DPRK, 
are slandering the North over its "nuclear development" and 
"attempt at communizing the South". This is the height of folly. 
  Although more than 40 years have passed since the conclusion 
of the Korean Armistice Agreement, the United States is still 
keeping up its military occupation of South Korea, far from 
withdrawing from there, and has reinforced its aggression 
forces in South Korea and ceaselessly staged new war provocation 
moves against the North together with the South Korean puppets. 
This itself is a flagrant violation of the Armistice Agreement. 
  It is ridiculous and impudent of the traitor Kim Yong-sam, a 
colonial puppet without even the military prerogative, to 
slander and meddle in the North's just negotiation proposal to 
establish a new peace arrangement which will replace the present 
armistice body. 
  In slandering the North, the traitor Kim Yong-sam sought to 
calm down sentiments of the people who turn out in 
anti-American, anti-"government" struggle and thus defuse his 
ever worsening ruling crisis. 
  But the truth cannot be concealed and the miserable end of 
the Kim Yong-sam puppet clique is inevitable. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

