<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK President Said `Inciting Confrontation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK President Said `Inciting Confrontation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0805083294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0805083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Puppet Traitor's Ballad of National Division"--KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim Yong-sam 
invited South Korean businessmen to a party Friday and drivelled 
that "fantastic view of reunification should be discarded," 
talking about the fictitious "North's desire to communize the 
South," "manufacturing of nuclear weapons" and the like, 
according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  His jargon is an unpardonable criminal utterance of inciting 
confrontation and disivion between the North and the South and 
an open challenge to the 70 million fellow countrymen ardently 
aspiring after the independent and peaceful reunification of the 
country. 
  His remarks are a ruse to justify the schemes for division 
and confrontation and a desperate attempt to calm down the 
fighting spirit of the South Korean people against him and 
bridge over the catastrophic crisis of the "civilian regime" by 
diverting elsewhere their attention. 
  This time the traitor let out a string of rubbish about 
"harmony between labor and capital," "industrial peace" and so 
on. It is, after all, nothing but a crafty jugglery to hush up 
South Korean workers who have turned out in the struggle for 
their existence, unable to eke out their livelihood any longer 
in the worst living position due to the colonial dependent 
economy. 
  The fact tells that unless the South Korean people 
resolutely 
break with such traitors as Kim Yong-sam, their independent 
demand and democratic rights cannot be guaranteed and the peace 
and peaceful reunification of the country cannot be realized. 
  The traitor Kim Yong-sam must step down at an early date as 
demanded by the people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

