<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Death of ROK Student in South Criticized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Death of ROK Student in South Criticized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905055094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0521 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905055094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Tragedy Produced by War-Maniacs" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Chang Tok-su, a 
third-year student of the business economics course of Sejong 
University in Seoul, was shot on the chest to death while in a 
drill of the "reserve forces" in South Korea some days ago. 
  NODONG SINMUN today criticizes it as another tragedy 
produced 
by the "civilian" regime's war hysterics against the North. 
  The news analyst says: 
  The puppet Defence Ministry described "pressure of his heart 
by a blank shot" as the cause of the death, but it was a 
ridiculous sophism to conceal its criminal act in forcing the 
university students to fire live cartridges in a war exercise. 
  Loud voices critical of the "civilian"-veiled war-maniacs 
who 
caused the death by driving students to a war exercise are 
ringing out from South Korea. 
  It is a treacherous act for the Kim Yong-sam group to drive 
out the students as a bullet shield in a war exercise against 
fellow countrymen. 
  The traitorous clique of Kim Yong-sam is staging war 
exercises almost every day, crying out for "tough posture" and 
"military countermove" toward the North. This inflicts 
immeasurable disasters on the people. 
  Unless the racket of North-South confrontation and war is 
stopped in South Korea, the people cannot be freed from 
disasters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

