<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese `Repression' of Chongnyon Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese `Repression' of Chongnyon Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905151194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1501 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The Zimbabwe Association 
of Democratic Lawyers on May 2 published a statement denouncing 
the repression of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans in Japan by the Japanese 
authorities. 
  The statement notes that the police of Japan which styles 
itself a law-governed country breaks into lawful Chongnyon 
organisations in broad daylight and commits outrages and 
gangsters, running about in packs, openly commit murder and 
violence against Koreans in Japan. 
  "This is an intolerable infringement upon the human rights 
of 
the Koreans in Japan, legitimate citizens overseas of the DPRK, 
and outrageous acts violating the international law," it notes 
and stresses: 
  "The Japanese authorities must promptly stop suppression of 
Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan and apologize for it". 
  It strongly demands that the Japanese authorities give up 
immediately their hostile policy against the DPRK and stop 
forthwith nuclear armament directed against it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

