<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Continues To Protest `Suppression' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Continues To Protest `Suppression' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905151594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1504 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 7 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
Officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans in Japan continue their protest 
against suppression by the Japanese police. 
  Officials and compatriots under the Osaka prefectural 
headquarters of Chongnyon on May 4 demanded that the Osaka 
prefectural police apologize for the crackdown on the Chongnyon 
organization at once and return the materials Lhich had been 
confiscated. 
  On the same day, compatriots of the Shibugawa section of the 
South branch of Chongnyon in Higashiosaka joined in the protest, 
led by a streamer inscribed with a slogan denouncing the police. 
  A symposium on the human rights of Koreans in Japan on May 2 
released a letter of protest condemning the repression by the 
Japanese police as a crackdown on the Koreans in Japan and 
violation of their human rights. 
  Branding the police search of Chongnyon as a political 
repression, the letter said such a repressive row itself is an 
expression of national discrimination and chauvinism. 

</TEXT>

