<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lao Military Delegation Continues Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lao Military Delegation Continues Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Choe Kwang Attends Talks </H4>

<F P=102> SK1005050394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0411 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1005050394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 10 (KCNA) -- Talks were held here 
Monday between a military delegation of the DPRK and a 
high-level delegation of the Ministry of National Defence of 
Laos. 
  Present on the Korean side were Choe Kwang, Politburo member 
of the C.C. [Central Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea and 
chief of the general staff of the Korean People's Army [KPA], 
Vice-Marshal Kim Kwang-chin and other generals and officers of 
the KPA, and on the opposite side were head of the delegation 
Choummali Sai-ngason, Politburo member of the C.C., the Lao 
People's Revolutionary Party and minister of national defence, 
Douangchai Phichit, deputy chief of the General Staff of the 
Laotian People's Army [LPA], Somphet Thipmala, director of the 
LPA General Logistics Department, Thongmani Thiphommachan, 
deputy director of the LPA General Political Department, and 
other members of the delegation. 
  The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

