<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Indian Communist Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Visit by Indian Communist Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    WPK Hosts Party 7 May </H4>

<F P=102> SK0805105194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0845 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0805105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
[C.C.] of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] gave a party on May 
7 for the delegation of the Communist Party of India (Marxist) 
on a visit to Korea. 
  Addressing the party, Secretary of the C.C., the WPK Hwang 
Chang-yop highly appreciated the Communist Party of India 
(Marxist) that is positively striving for the freedom and 
emancipation of the Indian people, the peace and security of 
Asia and the rest of the world and the cause of socialism, and 
expressed firm solidarity for it. 
  "The current situation makes it incumbent upon the communist 
and workers' parties to strengthen the bonds of international 
solidarity and collectively confront the anti-socialist 
offensives of the imperialists," he said, adding "the Workers' 
Party of Korea will, in the future, too, direct positive efforts 
to strengthening and developing the bonds of friendship and 
solidarity with the Communist Party of India (Marxist)". 
  Head of the delegation Jyoti Basu, member of the Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of India 
(Marxist) and prime minister of the West Bengal State, spoke at 
the party. 
  Noting Korea, a bulwalk of socialism, is the beacon of the 
world working class, he highly estimated the remarkable success 
achieved by the Korean people in the socialist construction 
under the guidance of respected Comrade Kim Il-song, the leader 
of the world communist movement, and the Workers' Party of Korea. 
  Pointing out that the Korean people are advancing under the 
uplifted banner of the chuche idea, he said: 
  Under the leadership of respected Comrade Kim Il-song and 
dear Comrade Kim Chong-il, the Korean people are thoroughly 
applying the principle of independence in politics, 
self-supporting in economy and self-reliance in defence. 
  Friendly and fraternal relations are existing between the 
Workers' Party of Korea and the Communist Party of India 
(Marxist) and the party members of the Communist Party of India 
(Marxist) are in high spirit over the socialism of Korea that is 
making a stride forward. 
  The spearhead of aggression of imperialism is now directed 
to 
socialism, he said, noting any moves of the U.S. imperialists 
can not bring the valiant revolutionaries of Korea to their 
knees. 
  He denounced the U.S. imperialists' unjustifiable pressure 
upon the Korean people with the fabrication of the "nuclear 
issue" and expressed solidarity for the Korean people's 
struggle, stressing that no one can check the advancement of 
people towards socialism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-52422 </DOCNO>
