<H3> <TI>   Further on Visit by Indian Communist Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Visit by Indian Communist Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Holds Talks With WPK Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> SK0905050694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0457 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905050694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Talks were held here 
Sunday between delegations of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] 
and the Communist Party of India (Marxist). 
  Present there on the Korean side were secretary Hwang 
Chang-yop and vice department director Kim Yang-kon of the WPK 
Central Committee and other officials concerned, and on the 
opposite side the delegation led by Jyoti Basu, Politburo member 
of the party Central Committee and prime minister of the west 
Bengal State. 
  At the talks the sides informed each other of their party 
activities and exchanged views on a series of matters of common 
concern. 
  Both sides declared that socialism is the future of mankind, 
stressing the need to develop the friendly relations between the 
two parties and strengthen solidarity with the socialist forces 
of the world. 
  The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

