<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nicaraguan President Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nicaraguan President Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905105294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1021 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Nicaraguan President 
Violeta Barrios de Chamorro and secretary general of the 
Sandinist National Liberation Front of Nicaragua Daniel Ortega 
Saavedra, when they met with the DPRK ambassador on April 29, 
praised the achievements of the Korean people in the building of 
socialism and expressed support to the DPRK's cause of national 
reunification. 
  "The present reality of Korea shows that the road to 
socialism, chosen by the Workers' Party and the people of Korea 
under the wise leadership of President Kim Il-song, is very 
just," the president said, adding: 
  The world is admiring the changes taking place in Korea 
today. 
  Korea has become the most powerful country by bringing into 
practice the principles of independence in politics, 
self-support in economy and self-reliance in defence. 
  Potentiality of the Korean people is inexhaustible and 
nobody 
can match the Korean people in strength. 
  We will fully support the Korean people's efforts for 
national reunification in the future, too. 
  Secretary General Daniel Ortega Saavedra said the great 
leader Comrade Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il put forward outstanding policies to repulse the 
maneuvers of the U.S. imperialists and their stooges to provoke 
another war and are wisely leading the Korean people's struggle 
for their materialization. 
  He voiced full support to the Workers' Party, the government 
and people of the DPRK in the struggle for the independent and 
peaceful reunification of the country and for a just solution to 
the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

