<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Receives Message From Malian Seminar </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Receives Message From Malian Seminar </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0805082194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0801 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0805082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received a message of greetings from the 
participants in a Malian joint seminar on the chuche idea and 
education held in Bamako. The message said: 
  President Kim Il-song founded the chuche idea, the idea of 
shaping the destiny of mankind, reflecting the independent 
demand and interest of the popular masses in the first period 
when he set out on the road of revolution and applied it to 
practical activities to build the socialist system centred on 
the popular masses in Korea. 
  The Korean-style socialism where the leader, the party and 
the masses are singleheartedly united gives a hope and courage 
to the world progressive people and clearly indicates the road 
ahead of the third world countries. 
  We extend firm solidarity with the heroic Korean people 
confidently advancing along the road of socialism chosen by 
themselves and express full support to the Korean people in 
their struggle to realize reunification of the country on the 
basis of the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole 
nation. 
  The message wished President Kim Il-song good health and a 
long life. 

</TEXT>

