<H3> <TI>   Papers Mark Anniversary of Relations With Chad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papers Mark Anniversary of Relations With Chad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0805090794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0829 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0805090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- Papers here today observe 
the 25th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic 
relations between the DPRK and Chad. 
  A bylined article of NODONG SINMUN says the establishment of 
diplomatic relations between the two countries at the 
ambassadorial level was a reflection of the common desire of the 
two peoples for mutual support and cooperation in the building 
of a new society. 
  Over the past 25 years the friendship between the two 
countries has developed and the understanding between the two 
peoples deepened, adds the paper. 
  The author of an article of MINJU CHOSON says: 
  Our people will strive to strengthen their relations with 
the 
Chadian people on the basis of the idea of independence, peace 
and friendship. 
  Our people wish the Chadian people greater success in their 
work, believing that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between the two countries will grow stronger and develop. 

</TEXT>

