<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former USSR Victory Shows Superiority of Socialism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former USSR Victory Shows Superiority of Socialism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905055294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0526 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Justice Is Sure To Win" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The great victory of the 
people of the former Soviet Union in the patriotic war (May 9, 
1945) was a demonstration of the superiority of the socialist 
system to the capitalist system and its invincible might, says 
NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined article today. 
  The article says: 
  By defeating fascist Germany in the past patriotic war, the 
people and Army of the former Soviet Union defended the 
socialist state, the first of its kind in the world, relieved 
peoples of many countries from the danger of fascist enslavement 
and greatly contributed to the human cause of liberation. 
  After the downfall of international fascism with the end of 
the Second World War, the popular masses, who had been the 
objects of history in the past, have now become the driving 
forces of history, shouldering the cause of independence. 
  But, the old forces of imperialism still remain and they are 
seeking the ambition for domination over the world as ever. 
  They are economically blockading and strangling and 
militarily threatening and crushing the countries that are going 
against them, while fostering national and regional 
contradictions, confrontations and division in different areas 
of the world. 
  The facts show that the aggressive nature of imperialism has 
never been changed and cannot be changed. 
  The obtaining situation requires the people the world over 
to 
unite for an active struggle against imperialism under the 
banner of anti-imperialist independence. 
  Only when the people of the world vigorously conduct the 
peace- defending movement against imperialism and war, will 
imperialism and dominationism become impotent and the people's 
cause of independence and socialism advance. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-52431 </DOCNO>
