<H3> <TI>   Foreign Media Cite Kim Il-song on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Media Cite Kim Il-song on Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1005045894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0409 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1005045894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 10 (KCNA) -- Foreign media reported 
famous works of the great leader President Kim Il-song "answers 
to the questions raised by the U.S. WASHINGTON TIMES news 
coverage group," "answers to the questions raised by the U.S. 
CNN news coverage group" and "answers to the questions raised by 
the NHK news coverage group." 
  The Yugoslav paper BORBA said the peaceloving remarks made 
recently by President Kim Il-song of the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea would be conducive to stabilizing the 
situation of the Korean peninsula. 
  The Algerian TV reported the works, screening a portrait of 
President Kim Il-song. 
  The Algerian papers LE MATIN, AL CHAAB, HABAR, AL MASSAA, EL 
MOUDJAHID, OPINION and EL WATAN, the Peruvian papers EXPRESO and 
EL COMERCIO, the Nicaraguan paper BARRICADA, the Syrian papers 
TISHRIN and AL BA'TH, the French papers LE MONDE and LA 
LIBERATION, the Thai paper BANGKOK POST, the Russian paper 
PRAVDA, the Vietnamese paper NHAN DAN, the Hungarian papers 
NEPSZABADSAG and NEPSZAVA, the German paper GENERAL ANZEIGER, 
the Polish paper TRIBUNA and the Indian paper HINDU and other 
leading papers and televisions of this country reported the 
works under the titles "President Kim Il-song Denies Nuclear 
Arms Development," "President Kim Il-song Declares North Korea 
Has No Nuclear Weapon," etc. 

</TEXT>

