<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Leaders Greet Kim Il-song </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905052094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0501 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905052094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song received congratulatory messages from 
foreign party leaders on his birthday. 
  Messages came from Eric Trevett, general secretary of the 
C.C. [Central Committee], the new Communist Party of Great 
Britain; Armando Villa Nueva, general secretary of the National 
Executive Committee of the American Popular Revolutionary 
Alliance of Peru; Luis Mateo Munos, general secretary of the 
Socialist Party of Peru; Gustavo Tablada, chairman of the 
Nicaraguan Socialist Party; Terence Marryshow, political leader 
of the Maurice Bishop Patriotic Movement of Grenada; George 
Belle, secretary general of the Barbados Workers' Party; Rene 
Mauge Mosquera, general secretary of the C.C., the Communist 
Party of Ecuador and chairman of the Broad Left Democratic Front 
of Ecuador; and Rigoberto Padilla Ruz, general secretary of the 
C.C., the Communist Party of Honduras. 
  They extend warmest congratulations to President Kim Il-song 
and wish him a long life in good health. 
  They also express firm solidarity with the Workers' Party 
and 
the people of Korea in the efforts for peace and reunification 
of the country. 
  President Kim Il-song received a congratulatory message also 
from the Executive Committee of the C.C., the Communist Party of 
Uruguay on his birthday. 

</TEXT>

