<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Parties, Organizations Issue Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Parties, Organizations Issue Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905104594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1016 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Delegates of political 
parties and organizations of different countries, who had 
attended the international seminar of revolutionary parties and 
organizations held in Brussels, made public a joint statement on 
May 4 denouncing the U.S. and its allies' moves to isolate and 
stifle Korea and supporting the Korean people's cause of 
national reunification. 
  The statement expressed deep apprehensions of the anti-DPRK 
campaign launched by the United States and its followers to 
isolate and stifle socialist Korea under the pretext of 
fictitious "nuclear suspicion". 
  It favoured the 10-point programme of the great unity of the 
whole nation which indicates a shortcut to Korea's reunification. 
  It demanded that the United States and its followers 
including the International Atomic Energy Agency stop at once 
their anti-DPRK, anti-socialist campaign going against the 
present trend of the world towards peace and justice. 
  It urged the South Korean authorities to send Kim In-so and 
Ham Se-hwan back to the North at once, set free all prisoners of 
conscience and accept the proposal for a convocation of national 
conference advanced by the North to achieve Korea's 
reunification in the 1990s. 
  It called upon political parties, organizations and 
progressive forces the world over to extend solidarity to the 
Workers' Party [WPK] and the people of Korea in their efforts 
for the defence of the socialist gains and for the independent 
and peaceful reunification of the country and conduct an 
international campaign to defend socialist Korea. 
  Meanwhile, the chairman of the Danish Communist Party (M-L), 
the chairman of the Communist Party of Germany, the general 
secretary of the All-Union Bolshevik Communist Party, the 
chairman of the Bulgarian Communist Party and the chairman of 
the Workers World Party of the United States, who attended the 
seminar, expressed full support to and solidarity with the WPK 
and the Korean people in their efforts for the building of 
socialism and the independent and peaceful reunification of the 
country, when they met the delegation of the Workers' Party of 
Korea. 

</TEXT>

