<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- The dear leader Comrade 
Kim Chong-il sent a letter to the staff of the DPRK Radio and 
Television Broadcasting Committee. 
  Upon receiving kind solicitude again from the dear leader 
for 
the strengthening of the broadcasting service, the staff of the 
committee had written him a letter carrying their unanimous 
resolution. 
  They noted in the letter that the dear leader always with a 
deep attention to broadcasting service has constantly shown 
loving care and warm favors for the broadcasting lorkers. They 
vowed to conduct broadcasting service strictly as intended by 
the party and the leader in order to repay the recent solicitude 
and devotedly work for the accomplishment of the cause of 
socialism, the revolutionary cause of chuche. 
  After reading the letter from the staff of the committee, 
Comrade Kim Chong-il sent the following letter to them: 
  "Thank you. 
  Let us all work hard together for victory in the 
revolutionary cause. 
  Kim Chong-il. April 23, 1994." 
  The letter of Comrade Kim Chong-il was conveyed to the staff 
of the DPRK Radio and Television Broadcasting Committee with a 
due ceremony at the committee Saturday. 

