<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Features Achievements in Railway Transport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Features Achievements in Railway Transport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0905114694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1031 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0905114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Railway workers of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea are greeting their holiday 
(May 11) with an increase in transportation. 
  According to data available at the Ministry of Railways, the 
daily freight haulage entering this month is 6,000 to 7,000 tons 
more than in the same period last month. 
  The General Bureau of Western Railways is topping the daily 
plan of freight turnover by 2,000 to 3,000 tons through well 
organized and commanded transportation. 
  The Kaechon General Bureau of Railways is overfulfilling the 
daily transport plan at an average of 107 percent. 
  The General Bureaus of Eastern and Northern Railways are 
carrying more freight than the plan by effectively controlling 
the locomotives, wagons and facilities. 
  Many railway stations including the Sariwon Youth Station, 
the Sinanju Youth Station, the Nanam Station and Pungnyon 
Station have hit the transport targets for the first half of the 
year more than two months earlier than schedule. 
  Railway builders have effected new innovations in the 
construction of railways including the Namdong-Onchon line. 

</TEXT>

