BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 10 KYODO -- Business leaders urged Prime 
Minister Tsutomu Hata to pass the overdue fiscal 1994 budget 
quickly in the Diet and take measures to help small and 
medium-size businesses suffering from the recession. 
  They also separately appealed to Hata to redistrict for a 
new 
single-seat electoral system under a Diet-approved overhaul of 
the current multiseat electoral system. 
  Hata replied the tasks must be done and will draw 
