  [Text] Tokyo, May 10 KYODO -- A business leader urged 
Japanese Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata on Tuesday [10 May] to 
achieve progress in economic reform to ensure domestic economic 
recovery and a better relationship with the United States. 
  "Steadfast progress in economic reform is vital to a sure 
turnaround in the economy and improvement in the Japan-U.S. 
