<H3> <TI>   Debate on East Timor Issues Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debate on East Timor Issues Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Official Regrets Planned Manila Meeting </H4>

<F P=102> BK1105141594 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1105141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia deeply regrets a plan for a conference on 
East Timor in Manila, the Philippines, to be held from 31 May to 
2 June. The director for foreign information, Irawan Abidin, 
stressed that Indonesia is not pleased with the plan in view of 
good Indonesian-Philippine ties, particularly within the context 
of ASEAN. Local newspapers have reported that a conference on 
East Timor sponsored by a number of non-governmental 
organizations will be held at the state-run University of the 
Philippines. 

</TEXT>

